              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".METALLIC MOLYBDENUM POWDER, ENRICHED IN MO-100, HAVING",
                " THE FOLLOWING ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION, THERMAL CAPTURE",
                " CROSS SECTION AND THERMAL CAPTURE CONTRIBUTION.",
                ".",
                ".                              CROSS        CAPTURE",
                "  MASS NO.    ABUNDANCE       SECTION     CONTRIBUTION",
                "              (PERCENT)         (B)         (PERCENT)",
                "    92       0.60+/-0.02       0.019          0.044",
                "    94       0.23+/-0.02       0.015          0.013",
                "    95       0.40+/-0.02    14.0+/-0.5     21.5+/-1.3",
                "    96       0.81+/-0.02     0.5+/-0.2      1.6+/-0.6",
                "    97       0.36+/-0.02     2.1+/-0.5      2.9+/-0.7",
                "    98       1.69+/-0.05   0.130+/-0.006   0.84+/-0.05",
                "   100       95.9+/-0.1    0.199+/-0.003   73.2+/-1.1",
                ".",
                " TWO TARGETS WITH EFFECTIVE THICKNESSES OF 37 AND 162",
                " MG/CM2 WERE USED FOR THE 10 - 250 KEV RANGE. THE TAR-",
                " GETS WERE SUSPENDED AT AN ANGLE OF 30 DEGREES TO THE",
                " AXIS OF THE VERTICAL NEUTRON BEAM WITHIN THE NEUTRON",
                " SHIELDING TUBE, IN FRONT OF THE DETECTORS. FOR THE",
                " HIGHER ENERGIES, THICKER TARGETS WERE USED."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " IN-BEAM GAMMA SPECTROSCOPY."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " GAMMA-RAYS IN THE RANGE 10 - 250 KEV WERE DE-",
                " TECTED WITH A 1.4 CM3 HPGE DETECTOR."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " THE SPECTRUM UP TO 1500 KEV WAS MEASURED WITH",
                " THE USE OF A 5.8 CM3 PLANAR AND A 38 CM3 TRUE COAXIAL",
                " GE(LI) DETECTOR. ENERGY AND RELATIVE EFFICIENCY CALI-",
                " BRATIONS WERE PERFORMED WITH AM-241, CO-57, BA-133 AND",
                " EU-152 RADIOACTIVE SOURCES.",
                "        THE HIGH-ENERGY GAMMA-RAYS WAS MEASURED WITH",
                " THE 38 CM3 TRUE COAXIAL GE(LI) DETECTOR AND A 10 CM3",
                " RECTANGULAR GE(LI) DETECTOR OF 0.5 CM DEPLETION DEPTH.",
                " GAMMA-RAYS OF 1261.8, 3683.9 AND 4945.3 KEV FROM NEU-",
                " TRON CAPTURE IN THE GRAPHITE TARGET CAPSULE WERE USED",
                " FOR ENERGY CALIBRATION. THESE LINES, IN ADDITION TO",
                " THOSE FROM THE N-14(N,G) REACTION, WERE USED FOR EFFI-",
                " CIENCY CALIBRATION."
              ]
            }
          ],
